<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 08 at 7:23PM MDT until August 08 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 800 PM MDT
FOR CROWLEY COUNTY...
At 722 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 16 miles northeast
of Pueblo Depot, or 25 miles northeast of Pueblo Airport, moving
southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Ordway and Sugar City.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
